Reasoning: The paper deals with the design and analysis of approximation algorithms for routing and scheduling problems, which are fundamental problems in combinatorial optimization. These problems are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), machine learning (cs.LG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
